President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2010 as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of exercise in maintaining good health and preventing chronic diseases. The President's Council on Physical Fitness and Sports offers resources and programs to motivate citizens of all ages to incorporate physical activity into their lives. Involvement in sports and recreational activities can teach valuable skills such as teamwork, fair play, and goal setting. The proclamation also highlights the issue of childhood obesity and the efforts of the Department of Health and Human Services, the President's Council, and First Lady Michelle Obama's "Let's Move" initiative to address this epidemic. The proclamation calls on all Americans to prioritize physical activity, fitness, and sports participation to improve their health and wellness.